userStories.notes:
Files:
- plugins/retool/src/index.ts (add configSchema property and ConfigSchema import)
- plugins/retool/package.json (add configSchema to opentabs field)

Context:
Retool has SaaS (retool.com) and self-hosted/on-prem deployments.

Current code in plugins/retool/src/index.ts:
```
import type { ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';
...
class RetoolPlugin extends OpenTabsPlugin {
  readonly name = 'retool';
  readonly description = 'OpenTabs plugin for Retool';
  override readonly displayName = 'Retool';
  readonly urlPatterns = ['*://*.retool.com/*'];
  override readonly homepage = 'https://retool.com';
```

Current package.json opentabs field:
```json
"opentabs": {
    "displayName": "Retool",
    "description": "OpenTabs plugin for Retool",
    "urlPatterns": [
      "*://*.retool.com/*"
    ]
}
```
Note: package.json is missing `homepage` — src/index.ts has it but package.json doesn't. Add it.

Changes:

1. In plugins/retool/src/index.ts:
   - Change `import type { ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';` to `import type { ConfigSchema, ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';`
   - Add after `override readonly homepage = 'https://retool.com';`:
     ```
     override readonly configSchema: ConfigSchema = {
       instanceUrl: {
         type: 'url' as const,
         label: 'Retool URL',
         description: 'The URL of your self-hosted Retool instance (e.g., https://retool.example.com). Leave empty to use retool.com.',
         required: false,
         placeholder: 'https://retool.example.com',
       },
     };
     ```

2. In plugins/retool/package.json, update the `opentabs` object to add `homepage` and `configSchema`:
   ```json
   "opentabs": {
     "displayName": "Retool",
     "description": "OpenTabs plugin for Retool",
     "urlPatterns": ["*://*.retool.com/*"],
     "homepage": "https://retool.com",
     "configSchema": {
       "instanceUrl": {
         "type": "url",
         "label": "Retool URL",
         "description": "The URL of your self-hosted Retool instance (e.g., https://retool.example.com). Leave empty to use retool.com.",
         "required": false,
         "placeholder": "https://retool.example.com"
       }
     }
   }
   ```

Constraints:
- Do NOT remove or change existing urlPatterns
- Do NOT set required: true
- Do NOT modify tool files, API files, or isReady logic
